President Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting with the Imo State governor, Rochas Okorocha at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Okorocha who was suspended from the All Progressives Congress (APC) over anti-party, arrived the State House, around 1:pm and went straight to the President’s office. The governor, the Senator-elect for Imo West senatorial district has been facing serious battle with the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) over his certificate of return. The commission is yet to issue him the certificate of return. Details soon Okorocha to INEC: Release my Certificate of Return As Okorocha battles for political survival… Imo West:  Returning Officer not under duress – Observers